                <h3>Upsides:</h3>
                <p>
                  Yumemi has the best movement speed and attack speed possible, which allow her to properly chain enemies with ease (because she can move towards enemies
                  and destroy them as efficiently as possible). Her L1 even complements this because it has the potential to automatically chain enemies, making her a rather
                  beginner friendly character for people that haven't yet mastered the art of enemy formations.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Her boss is a monster: it has an aiming pattern and one that spawns tons of cross. It also has rather large HP (130) making it hard to fully cancel with a bomb
                  and basic shots (it would persist for a bit).
                </p>
                <p>
                  Said cross ex attacks are pretty good as well because of how they persist on the screen, preventing movement. They take a lot of space and can corner opponents,
                  stack together and they spawn relatively fast which gives the enemy only a short notice to get out of the way.
                </p>
                <h3>Downsides:</h3>
                <p>
                  Yumemi really only has one big downside and it his her L2/L3 patterns which are really easy to dodge, even at higher levels. Because of that, I'd say it is advised
                  to instead keep gauge energy to reflect a boss attack with her own, or for her gauge hyper.
                </p>
