                </p>
                <p>
                  Her L2/L3 patterns come sideways and are a bit tricky to dodge. Her boss is pretty great, as it fires ex attacks that are partially used (yellow / red),
                  that stay less on the screen than the typical ex attack but resists bombs.
                </p>
                <h3>Downsides:</h3>
                <p>
                  Mima's L2 is actually a pretty good target for reversals due to how packed it is: this means using it might be punishable if the opponent has a chain
                  of enemies properly placed to take advantage of it. Aside from that, her only real weakness is a below average charge speed.
