                  Chiyuri has the highest HP boss in the game, and that makes it pretty resilient to bombing, meaning it won't instantly dispawn even as the players
                  fires basic shots during the bomb. It also has pretty rough patterns and can go down in the middle of the screen.
                </p>
                <p>
                  She has good speed and charge speed, and a pretty great L1 that can be used to damage boss attacks (4 of them can actually kill a boss). Said L1
                  can start chains decently well, and be used as a defensive tool since it follows her for an extended time.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Her ex attack is alright because it can wall off the opponent, in particular when the boss spawns because it sends over a lot of them.
                </p>
                <h3>Downsides:</h3>
                <p>
                  Chiyuri's L2/L3 are easy to stream, and cancel in the case of her L2, making them a non-issue unless you manage to corner the opponent with them.
                  Her L4 also spawns a lot of pellets, which is detrimental and makes it weak to boss reversal as the enemy gets to score more by cancelling them.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Her L1 also has a fatal flaw: she cannot charge up her gauge, bomb or trigger her hyper while it happens, meaning using it too much can actually be
                  dangerous, in particular if the screen is dense with non-cancellable bullets.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Despite her ex attack being decent, the fact it takes a while to spawn also makes it usually easy to dodge.
                </p>
