                <h3>Downsides:</h3>
                <p>
                  Reimu has a terrible base shot speed, which can get covered by her defensive L1 during spell wars. However, said L1 is itself
                  really bad offensively speaking because it cannot trigger combo chains by itself, instead deleting most ennemies on the field.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="modal" x-show="openModal=='rikako'">
            <div class="modal-content" @click.outside="openModal=''" @keydown.escape.window="openModal=''">
              <div class="modal-header">
                <h2>Rikako Asakura</h2>
              </div>
              <div class="modal-body">
                <table class="noborders">
                  <tr>
                    <td>
                      <div class="portrait">
                        <img src="/images/podd/rikako.png">
                      </div>
                    </td>
                    <td>
                      <table class="stats noborders">
                        <tr>
                          <td>
                            Movement Speed
                          </td>
                          <td class="value">
                            <progress value="4.5" max="5.0"/>
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                          <td>
                            Attack Speed
                          </td>
                          <td class="value">
                            <progress value="5" max="5"/>
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                          <td>
                            Charge Speed
                          </td>
                          <td class="value">
                            <progress value="1" max="5"/>
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                          <td>
                            Boss HP
                          </td>
                          <td class="value">
                            110
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                      </table>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                </table>
                <h3>Upsides:</h3>
                <p>
                  Her L1 is mainly useful defensively, but she can fire basic shots as it goes up the screen, allowing her to chain in two times at once and
                  prolong active chains. The fact it is slow is a bit detrimental to chains however, as it will keep hitting enemies, destroying them before any
                  explosion does.
                </p>
                <p>
                  The version of this L1 she uses during her hyper is however much better, because she can instead just move slightly towards a pack of enemies
                  and hit one of them with the tip to trigger an explosion chain. Said hyper actually has a glitch with a rare usecase: if Rikako's hyper is active
                  as she wins a round, she will keep her L1 gravitating around her for the next round (until she triggers the hyper again and it ends). While this
                  disables her gauge fully, it is still worth it due to how good it can be at chaining things.
                </p>
                <p>
                  She has a pretty strong boss attack because it can fire non cancellable flurry of bullets in oblique directions,
                  making them hard to dodge in a game without focus (you need to get around them and gap is small).
                </p>
                <h3>Downsides:</h3>
                <p>
                  Rikakos's ex attack isn't very dangerous: it is made up of some kind of chainsaw that slides down the screen, and can target an opponent if they get
                  too close. However, it is relatively small, and because this game has a maximum number of simultaneous ex attacks of 8, it is rarely an issue.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Her super slow charge speed hinder her, and her goot basic attack shot speed doesn't really make all that much for it because it has a small hitbox,
                  meaning it is still somewhat hard to reliably deal damage with it.
                </p>
                <p>
                  The pattern of her boss attack mentioned as an upside also actually only spawns non cancellable bullets if it has been upgraded enough, meaning
                  it is initially pretty weak to boss reversals.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="modal" x-show="openModal=='marisa'">
            <div class="modal-content" @click.outside="openModal=''" @keydown.escape.window="openModal=''">
              <div class="modal-header">
                <h2>Marisa Kirisame</h2>
              </div>
              <div class="modal-body">
                <table class="noborders">
                  <tr>
                    <td>
                      <div class="portrait">
                        <img src="/images/podd/marisa.png">
                      </div>
                    </td>
                    <td>
                      <table class="stats noborders">
                        <tr>
                          <td>
                            Movement Speed
                          </td>
                          <td class="value">
                            <progress value="4.0" max="5.0"/>
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                          <td>
                            Attack Speed
                          </td>
                          <td class="value">
                            <progress value="4" max="5"/>
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                          <td>
                            Charge Speed
                          </td>
                          <td class="value">
                            <progress value="3" max="5"/>
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                          <td>
                            Boss HP
                          </td>
                          <td class="value">
                            110
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                      </table>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                </table>
                <h3>Upsides:</h3>
                <p>
                  Marisa's main strength is her ex attack which takes time to spawn, but walls a bit in corridors, forcing vertical movmement.
                  It can also actually spawn in numbers above the usual maximum 8 ex attacks limit (because the ex attack itself is the blue
                  circle spawning the laser, which disappears after firing said laser).
                </p>
                <p>
                  Similarly to Chyuri, Marisa's L1 is pretty decent at chaining enemies and killing the boss, but where it really shines is at
                  sliding across the screen to defensively delete enemies. In particular, it is very great at dealing with packs of ghosts sent her way.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Her L2/L3 are OK, they spawn cross corridors that go around the opponent, making it harder to move too much. They combine well with the lasers
                  into an offense that mainly plans to restrict the enemy's options. 
                </p>
                <p>
                  Finally, she also has decent stats: good movement and attack speed, above average charge speed.
                </p>
                <h3>Downsides:</h3>
                <p>
                  Marisa's biggest issue is that she has a bad boss attack. Its patterns aren't great, but its main issue is that it waits for a long while inbetween
                  different patterns, and when it spawns, meaning it lets quite a long time for the opponent to score and reverse it, or plan how they will kill
                  enemies in order to cancel the pellets it sends over. Because of that, her offense suffers tremendously, explaining her low tier spot on this list.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Her L1 also suffers from the same issue as Chiyuri's: she cannot shoot, bomb or activate her hyper during it.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="modal" x-show="openModal=='kana'">
            <div class="modal-content" @click.outside="openModal=''" @keydown.escape.window="openModal=''">
              <div class="modal-header">
                <h2>Kana Anaberal</h2>
              </div>
              <div class="modal-body">
                <table class="noborders">
                  <tr>
                    <td>
                      <div class="portrait">
                        <img src="/images/podd/kana.png">
                      </div>
                    </td>
                    <td>
                      <table class="stats noborders">
                        <tr>
                          <td>
                            Movement Speed
                          </td>
                          <td class="value">
                            <progress value="3.5" max="5.0"/>
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                          <td>
                            Attack Speed
                          </td>
                          <td class="value">
                            <progress value="2" max="5"/>
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                          <td>
                            Charge Speed
                          </td>
                          <td class="value">
                            <progress value="5" max="5"/>
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                          <td>
                            Boss HP
                          </td>
                          <td class="value">
                            100
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                      </table>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                </table>
                <h3>Upsides:</h3>
                <p>
                  Kana's main upside is her charge speed which combines well with her L1, which is great at dealing point blank damage and can actually be used
                  decently well to kill boss attacks. It can also be used at bigger distances to start chains from two sides of the screen for a few enemy formations.
                </p>
                <h3>Downsides:</h3>
                <p>
                  She has a terrible ex attack, L2/L3 and boss attack, which all together taken combine into the worst offense of the game. Sadly, this is likely one of
                  the most important part of a character in a Phantasmagoria game, thus explaining on its own why she sits at the bottom of this tier list.
                </p>
                <p>
                  The ex attack works a bit like Mystia's in PoFV (a bird that spawns bullets). It at least cannot be cancelled but it spawns bullets with a big gap
                  inbetween them, making them rather useless, unless stacked up.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Her L2/L3 leave are static and leave big gaps in the center of the field: they can thus easily be dodged. Finally, her boss attack has a few patterns
                  spawning lines of noncancellable bullets in a circle, that only divide the screen a bit, but are also trivial to dodge. It also has low HP.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

